reative and non-dogmatic three-aspects model of planning for young people leaving care. A valuable resource for practitioners, researchers and educators, this book puts forward a powerful case to think more broadly and flexibly about transition planning with care-leavers, placing the voices of young people at its heart.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Work.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311129965540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447368359zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447368359/original  a978-3-11-129965-5  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA